{
  "texts": [
    "Granting the government broad power to determine truth can risk overreach and censorship, potentially stifling legitimate dissent (Access Now, 2023).",
    "India's experience highlights the tension in regulating disinformation in a democracy -how to curb dangerous falsehoods at scale without undermining civil liberties.",
    "The high volume of content in India (over 800 million internet users by 2025) also makes enforcement difficult, and misinformation (often via WhatsApp forwards in myriad local languages) has continued to spark violence and social unrest in recent years.",
    "Thus, while India's regulatory strategy enables swift removal of content, it also underscores the need for complementary approaches like community fact-checking and media literacy to address root causes of belief in rumors.",
    "China's authoritarian information control regime has taken a markedly different approach, focusing on stringent preemptive regulations to prevent AI misuse."
  ]
}